					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">DPCM = delta pulse code modulation<br />DMC = delta modulation channel<br /><br />The DMC has a 7-bit &quot;current value&quot; register. Raw PCM playback feeds individual samples to this register. A program may also write once to this register before starting background playback of a DPCM sample, producing the pops common in Konami NSFs.<br /><br />I've written tools to encode and decode DPCM in Python. This should give you an idea of exactly how it would sound. Are you capable of running Python programs on your computer? What operating system (Windows, Linux, or OS X) does your computer run?</div>

